          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Null pointer dereference from double-increment bug in create_user_account(): userid_next is incremented twice per call (once in ua->userid = userid_next++ and once in return userid_next++), storing the account at accounts[userid_next] after the first increment. This leaves accounts[0] and all even-indexed slots as NULL. Any call to is_admin() or username() with an even-numbered user ID passes the bounds check but dereferences a NULL pointer."
